%% Feast Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>Controller Manager
    participant Online as Online Store<br/>80/TCP HTTP or 443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Offline as Offline Store<br/>80/TCP HTTP or 443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as Registry Server<br/>gRPC 6570/6571, REST 6572/6573
    participant DB as DB Backend<br/>(Redis/PostgreSQL/etc.)
    participant CronPod as CronJob Pod<br/>(ose-cli)
    participant Notebook as Kubeflow Notebook

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 1: FeatureStore CR Reconciliation
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch/Informer notification<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployments, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, PVCs, SA, RBAC,<br/>CronJobs, Routes<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created

    Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Online Feature Serving
    User->>Online: GET/POST features<br/>HTTP/80 or HTTPS/443<br/>Auth: K8s RBAC / OIDC / None
    Online->>DB: Query features<br/>Protocol: varies<br/>Auth: user-configured
    DB-->>Online: Feature values
    Online-->>User: Feature response

    Note over CronPod,Operator: Flow 3: CronJob Execution
    K8sAPI->>CronPod: Schedule CronJob<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    CronPod->>Operator: oc exec into Feast pod
    Note right of CronPod: Executes:<br/>feast apply<br/>feast materialize-incremental

    Note over Notebook,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Notebook Integration
    User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>with feast annotation
    K8sAPI->>Operator: NotebookConfigMapReconciler<br/>watches Notebook CRs
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read FeatureStore CR &<br/>client ConfigMaps
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create feast-config ConfigMap<br/>in notebook namespace
    K8sAPI-->>Notebook: ConfigMap mounted in notebook
